So how does eBook 4 Sale save you from the above two scenarios?  Simple.  We use the "World Wide Web" as our means of distribution, and "Shareware" as our means of selling your ebook. The web's soul purpose is to move data around. This data can be your ebook. Using eBook 4 Sale is more like the second scenario without the printing costs and distributing problems. Your self-publishing your ebook under the concept of "Shareware." eBook 4 Sale allows you to limit what you are allowing your customer to see, which is what will inspire them to pay your registration fee.

Let's say, for example, you have scanned in all of your art boards and/or made text files for each page of your novel. Add these files to eBook 4 Sale and generate your own program. This is your "software" to sell! You can now take your ebook and upload it to other online services (like AOL), web sites (like www.download.com), and your own web site.

The other benefit to this approach is that you are the one in control. You decide what your ebook is to be and your vision stands. There is no one else in the picture to force changes onto your work.

