Don't let the word secure mislead you. All secure means is  that once the data is received by your online providers email service, it is safe from being accessed by others. We still need to protect the credit card information that is transmitted from your customers' browser to your online providers servers. For this you will need an SSL Certificate (Secure Socket Layer). Once you have that, your online provider can set you up with a "Secured Web Page." This is the page you use to take your credit card orders. I'm just giving a quick overview on this subject because you'll need to talk to your online provider to see what services they provide.
